{
  "_DO_NOT_USE": "THIS SPEC IS WRONG ON PURPOSE. It is kept as evidence, not as a reference. A client generated from it would hard-fork itself off Dogecoin mainnet at block 145,000.",
  "_what_is_wrong": "It FLATTENS Core's consensus fork tree. It reports a single consensus regime per network -- CMainParams.nPowTargetTimespan = 14400, the pre-Digishield value -- and has no post-145000 regimes at all. Real Core mainnet has three (consensus@0 -> digishield@145000 -> auxpow@371337).",
  "_why_it_is_here": "It looks correct. It parses. Every value in it is a real value. That is what 'confidently wrong' means, and it is the failure this repo exists to make impossible. A wrong artifact you can open and read is worth more than a paragraph claiming one existed.",
  "_source": "sample_chainparams.cpp",
  "_source_note": "Generated by the CURRENT extractor from sample_chainparams.cpp -- a hand-written, flat, pre-tree mirror of Core kept in this repo's root. It is NOT real Core output. The flattening comes from the flat input, which is what makes it a faithful reproduction of the v1 bug: v1 flattened real Core the same way this flat sample is flat by construction.",
  "_provenance_note": "core_commit is null and that is correct: this did not come from a Core checkout, so there is no Core commit to cite. An earlier extractor would have stamped this repo's own HEAD here -- a fabricated pin. See commit 'Refuse to stamp core_commit when the source isn't Core'.",
  "_why_verify_selection_passes_this": "verify_selection.py returns OK on this file. That is correct and worth understanding: it proves the sorted-array argmax matches Core's BST walk FOR THE TREE IN THE SPEC. Here the tree is a single node, so the proof is trivially true -- and useless, because the flattening already happened upstream in extraction. A proof about a spec cannot detect what the spec lost before it arrived. gen_consensus_c.py DOES refuse this file, via the field-coverage gate. Green from one check is not green.",
  "_regenerate": "./extract_chainparams.py sample_chainparams.cpp -o docs/flattened_v1_spec.json",
  "_note": "NOT generated from Dogecoin Core. See _DO_NOT_USE and _source_note. This file is deliberately wrong and exists only as evidence.",
  "_provenance": {
    "file_sha256": "9cbb77afd02801e6c0f4edc43e0100d980a7b3cebc20e0af37b917058aeac3d5",
    "core_commit": null,
    "_warning": "not extracted from a Dogecoin Core checkout: /tmp/p2 has no configure.ac defining _CLIENT_VERSION_MAJOR. core_commit is deliberately null -- stamping this repo's HEAD would fabricate a pin. file_sha256 still identifies the exact bytes parsed."
